Cell["\<\
Good code should have a structure that\[CloseCurlyQuote]s easy to read. But \
sometimes there are details that you have to include in the code, but that \
get in the way of seeing its main point. In Wolfram Notebooks, there\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s a convenient way to deal with this: iconize the details. \
\
\>", "Text",
 Editable->False,
 Deletable->False,
 ShowCellBracket->False],

Cell["Make a plot with a long sequence of options specified:", "CodeCaption",
 Editable->False,
 Deletable->False,
 ShowCellBracket->False],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
ListLinePlot[Table[Prime[n]/n,{n,100}],Frame->True, \
PlotStyle->Orange,Filling->Axis, 
FillingStyle->LightPurple,AspectRatio->1/3,Mesh->All]\
\>", "Input",
 Deletable->False,
 CellLabel->"In[29]:="],

